<DocsLayout title="API Reference" description="Complete LeadEcho REST API documentation — all endpoints, authentication, and response formats.">
  <h1>API Reference</h1>

  <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
    The LeadEcho REST API is served at <code>/api/v1/</code>. All endpoints require authentication
    unless marked as public. The API returns JSON for all responses.
  </p>

  <h2>Authentication</h2>

  <p>Two authentication modes are supported:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Mode</th>
        <th>Header</th>
        <th>Used By</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>JWT Bearer</td>
        <td><code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Dashboard, all user-facing endpoints</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Extension Key</td>
        <td><code>X-Extension-Key: ext_01hx...</code></td>
        <td>Chrome extension endpoints only</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Register</h3>
  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

&#123; "email": "user@example.com", "password": "strongpass123" &#125;</code></pre>

  <h3>Login</h3>
  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

&#123; "email": "user@example.com", "password": "strongpass123" &#125;

# Response sets httpOnly JWT cookie + returns user object</code></pre>

  <h3>Google OAuth</h3>
  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/auth/google           # Redirects to Google
GET /api/v1/auth/google/callback  # Google redirects here after auth</code></pre>

  <h3>Current User</h3>
  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;</code></pre>

  <h3>Logout</h3>
  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;</code></pre>

